    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-10-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="481" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <head>No. 26.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">L. S. Sackville
                                    West</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-10-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 13,
                                1887</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your note
                            of yesterday, in relation to the cases of seizure of the British
                            schooners <hi rend="italic">Onward, Carolena</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Thornton</hi>, in Behring Sea, by United States revenue vessels, in
                            August, 1886, and also your instructions to include by similar
                            representations the cases of the British Columbian vessels <hi rend="italic">Grace, Dolphin</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">W. P.
                                Sayward</hi>, seized by the United States revenue authorities in
                            Behring Sea, with notification that Her Britannic Majesty’s Government
                            reserves all right to compensation on behalf of the owners and crews of
                            the above-mentioned vessels. The affidavit of the mate of the <hi rend="italic">W. P. Sayward</hi> has been read, and the facts
                            therein stated will be at once investigated.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
